ApexExtlCalloutEventLog.name: ApexExtlCalloutEventLog
ApexExtlCalloutEventLog.description: Apex Extl Callout EventLog represent external data callouts via custom adapters for Salesforce Connect.

ExecutionTime.description: The end-to-end Apex execution time in milliseconds.

FetchTime.description: Duration (in milliseconds) it takes to retrieve the query results from the external system.

IsSuccess.description: Indicates whether the query was successful (true) or not (false).

Message.description: Error or warning message associated with the failed call.

ObjectType.description: The type of event. The value is always BulkApi2.

QueryFilter.description: Field expressions to filter the rows to return. Corresponds to WHERE in SOQL queries.

QueryLimit.description: Maximum number of rows to return for a query. Corresponds to LIMIT in SOQL queries.

QueryOffset.description: Number of rows to skip when paging through a result set. Corresponds to OFFSET in SOQL queries.

QueryOrderBy.description: Field or column to use for sorting query results, and whether to sort the results in ascending (default) or descending order. Corresponds to ORDER BY in SOQL queries.

QuerySelect.description: Comma-delineated list of fields being queried. Corresponds to SELECT in SOQL queries.

RequestIdentifier.description: The unique ID of a single transaction. A transaction can contain one or more events. Each event in a given transaction has the same RequestIdentifier. For example: 3nWgxWbDKWWDIk0FKfF5DV.

RowCount.description: Total number of records in the result set.

RowsFetched.description: Number of rows fetched by the callout.

Subqueries.description: Number of subqueries this query has been split into.

Throughput.description: Number of records retrieved in one second.

Timestamp.description: The access time of Salesforce services in GMT. For example, 2020-01-20T19:12:26.965Z. Milliseconds are the most granular setting.

TotalTime.description: How long it takes (in milliseconds) to prepare and execute the query and to retrieve the query results.

UserIdentifier.description: The ID of the user whoâ€™s using Salesforce services through the UI or the API. For example: 00530000009M943.
